docs_sync_for_code_changes:
  description: "Check whether DeepWork documentation for the standalone Pi package needs updates after code changes."
  lifecycle:
    cadence: pull_request
  match:
    include:
      - "src/**/*.ts"
      - "extensions/**/*.ts"
      - "test/**/*.ts"
      - "*.ts"
      - "*.js"
      - "*.mjs"
    exclude:
      - "node_modules/**"
      - "coverage/**"
      - "dist/**"
  review:
    strategy: matches_together
    additional_context:
      all_changed_filenames: true
    reference_files:
      - path: "README.md"
        description: "DeepWork standalone Pi package documentation"
      - path: "docs/README_REVIEWS.md"
        description: "DeepWork Reviews documentation"
      - path: "docs/native-bridge.md"
        description: "Native bridge documentation"
      - path: "skills/README.md"
        description: "Packaged skill documentation index"
    instructions: |
      Code changed in the standalone DeepWork Pi package. Review the changed files and decide whether documentation should also be updated.

      Documentation files to consider include `README.md`, files under `docs/`, and relevant skill or prompt documentation. Flag a finding if the code changes add, remove, rename, or materially change user-facing behavior, native tools, command behavior, event integration, review behavior, workflow semantics, schemas, configuration, setup, validation, or packaged skills/prompts but the relevant documentation was not updated. Do not require documentation changes for purely internal refactors, test-only maintenance, or behavior-preserving cleanup.
